## Phase 0: Read & Orient

Read the GDD. Then extract the 5 context anchors. Present what you found (and what's missing) via AskUserQuestion:

> **[Re-ground]** Reviewing `[GDD name]` for `[game title]` on `[branch]`.
>
> Here's what I found in your GDD:
>
> | Context Anchor | Status | What I Found |
> |---|---|---|
> | Genre & Platform | ✅/❌ | {found or "not stated"} |
> | Target Session Length | ✅/❌ | {found or "not stated"} |
> | Monetization Model | ✅/❌ | {found or "not stated"} |
> | Target Audience | ✅/❌ | {found or "not stated"} |
> | Design Pillars | ✅/❌ | {found or "not stated — I need these to validate design coherence"} |
>
> {For each ❌, provide a best-guess with [inferred] tag if possible.}
>
> **Are these correct?** Any I should update before we start the review?
> A) Correct — proceed to mode selection
> B) Fix these: {user corrects}

**STOP.** Wait for confirmation. If any anchor is missing and can't be inferred, ask ONE question per missing anchor. Do NOT batch.

Example for missing platform:
> Your GDD doesn't specify the target platform. This matters because it changes which sections I prioritize.
>
> A) **Mobile** — I'll weight retention and economy heavily
> B) **PC / Console** — I'll weight core loop depth and narrative
> C) **Web** — I'll weight accessibility and session flexibility
> D) **Multiple / undecided** — I'll use balanced weights
>
> RECOMMENDATION: Choose based on where your FIRST players will be. You can add platforms later.
> Player Impact: 8/10 — platform shapes every other design decision.

**STOP.** Wait for answer. Repeat for each missing anchor ONE AT A TIME.

### Mode Selection

After ALL anchors are established, ask the user to select a review mode:

**AskUserQuestion:**

> Now I know the context. Let me calibrate the review.
>
> Different games have different priorities — a mobile gacha lives or dies on its economy; a narrative PC game lives or dies on pacing. Choose the mode so I focus on what matters most for YOUR game.
>
> RECOMMENDATION: {Choose based on the platform/genre anchors just confirmed. State why.}
>
> - **A) Mobile / Casual** — Heavy weight on retention hooks (D1/D7/D30), economy balance, session fit, monetization ethics. Core loop must complete in <2 min. Player Impact: 9/10 if F2P.
> - **B) PC / Console** — Heavy weight on core loop depth, mastery curve, narrative integration, session arc. Economy secondary unless live-service. Player Impact: 9/10 if premium.
> - **C) Multiplayer / Competitive** — Heavy weight on balance fairness, matchmaking, counterplay, anti-cheat surface. Economy evaluated for P2W risk. Player Impact: 9/10 if PvP-centric.
> - **D) Narrative** — Heavy weight on pacing, branching, emotional arc, ludonarrative consonance. Economy and retention secondary. Player Impact: 9/10 if story-driven.
> - **E) Tabletop / Physical** — Heavy weight on rules clarity, component ergonomics, session length, player count scaling. No digital economy. Player Impact: 9/10 if physical game.

**STOP.** Wait for mode selection before starting any section review.

### Mode Weight Adjustments

| Section | A: Mobile | B: PC/Console | C: Multiplayer | D: Narrative | E: Tabletop |
|---------|-----------|---------------|----------------|--------------|-------------|
| 1. Core Loop | 25% | 30% | 25% | 15% | 25% |
| 2. Progression & Retention | 25% | 20% | 15% | 15% | 15% |
| 3. Economy | 25% | 10% | 20% | 5% | 10% |
| 4. Player Motivation | 10% | 15% | 15% | 30% | 20% |
| 5. Risk Assessment | 5% | 10% | 10% | 10% | 10% |
| 6. Cross-Consistency | 10% | 15% | 15% | 25% | 20% |

