## Review Pacing

**After completing EACH section**, present the section score and ask before continuing:

> **Section {N} — {name}: {score}/10**
> {1-sentence summary of the biggest finding}
>
> A) **Continue to Section {N+1}** — {next section name}
> B) **Go back** — I want to address an issue from this section first
> C) **Fast-forward** — skip to the score summary (I've seen enough)
> D) **Stop here** — save progress, I'll come back later

**STOP.** Wait for answer.

If user chooses C (fast-forward): Complete remaining sections with AUTO-only analysis (flag issues but don't ask), then present the full score summary. Mark review as `DONE_WITH_CONCERNS — fast-forwarded from Section {N}`.

If user chooses D (stop): Present partial score, list what hasn't been reviewed, and note which sections to pick up next time.

### Forcing Question Smart Routing

Each section says "must ask at least 2" forcing questions. But don't always ask the same ones. Route based on the GDD's state:

| GDD State | Focus Forcing Questions On |
|-----------|---------------------------|
| GDD is early (many ⚠️/❌ from import) | Foundational questions — "Can you describe the core loop?" "Who comes back tomorrow?" |
| GDD is detailed but untested | Validation questions — "Have you watched someone play?" "What breaks at 2x scale?" |
| GDD is post-playtest revision | Depth questions — "What did playtesters do that surprised you?" "What did you change since last review?" |

Determine state from `docs/gdd.md`'s GDD Status section (written by `/game-import`) or by reading the GDD's depth.

